<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-46-0135 </DOCNO><TEXT>The amounts of crude oil, gas and oil products regarding exports fromAlgeria in 1980s are described and trends in the balance of internationaltrade and debts to foreign countries are summarized. After brief presentationon the history of oil and gas industries, the author reviewed the trendsin oil and gas including: exploration and development of oil, productionand exports of crude oil, oil prices, production and export of condensates,production/export/prices of gas and gas markets. The Algerian policyof oil and gas remains unchanged after the rapid fall in oil prices.The policy for resources diversification and increased added values ofhydrocarbons is promoted today toward two targets: Maximizing the incomefrom the hydrocarbon resources and securing stable markets under thedepressed oil prices. Effective management of energy demand and a simulationof resource exploration and development are urgently required for maintainingoil and gas exports. (1 fig, 19 tabs, 6 refs)</TEXT></DOC>